text: Fred L. Muhl (April 3, 1880 – October 23, 1954) was an American football, basketball and baseball coach. He served as the head football (1906, 1909–1920}, head men's basketball (1910–1921) and head baseball (1926) coach at Illinois Wesleyan University. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1880 births Category:1954 deaths Category:American football quarterbacks Category:Illinois Fighting Illini football players Category:Illinois Wesleyan Titans football coaches Category:Illinois Wesleyan Titans men's basketball coaches Category:Illinois Wesleyan Titans baseball coaches Category:Players of American football from Illinois Category:Sportspeople from Bloomington, Illinois
